# AWS EBS Practice - Day 2

This repository contains my Day 2 practice tasks related to AWS EBS (Elastic Block Store), including attaching and mounting EBS volumes to EC2 instances.

## 🛠️ Tasks Done

- Created and attached a new EBS volume to an EC2 instance
- Formatted the volume using `mkfs`
- Mounted the volume to a directory
- Verified persistence after reboot

## 📂 Folder Structure

- `scripts/`: Shell scripts used in the process
- `notes/`: Linux commands and steps used
- `screenshots/`: Output of CLI or EC2 steps

## 📜 Basic Commands Used

```bash
lsblk
sudo mkfs -t ext4 /dev/xvdf
sudo mkdir /data
sudo mount /dev/xvdf /data
df -h
